16 generously contribute their time and effort to assist artisans, set up and break down booths,
17 and welcome visitors with warmth and hospitality; and
18 WHEREAS, Splash Festivals works in close collaboration with the City of Norcross,
19 including the police department and city staff, to ensure a safe and enjoyable experience for
20 festival attendees; and
21 WHEREAS, through their unique approach to event planning, Splash Festivals has
22 established a strong reputation for producing high-quality festivals that engage communities,
23 attract thousands of visitors, and celebrate the spirit of the arts; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable company be
25 appropriately honored.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize and commend Splash Festivals for its many outstanding
28 contributions on behalf of the citizens of this state as well as extend best wishes for continued
29 success.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
32 Splash Festivals.
